  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6600.72 sitting just below the max positive gamma wall at 6605 (24.6B), dealers are likely selling into any strength as they hedge their long gamma positions, creating immediate resistance. The PIN regime with massive positive gamma concentration between 6605-6620 should contain upside moves and encourage mean reversion back toward the 6590-6605 range. Watch 6590 closely as the key negative gamma floor - any break below triggers dealer buying that could spark a sharp bounce, while the 6605 level acts as the primary sell zone.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect price to get pinned between 6590-6605 with dealers capping rallies near current levels.",
